verses.text:
Also Cyrus the king brought forth the vessels of the house
of the \nd LORD\nd*, which Nebuchadnezzar had brought forth out of
Jerusalem, and had put them in the house of his gods;

And by the good hand of our God upon us they brought us a
man of understanding, of the sons of Mahli, the son of Levi, the
son of Israel; and Sherebiah, with his sons and his brethren, eighteen;

Also of the Nethinims, whom David and the princes had appointed
for the service of the Levites, two hundred and twenty Nethinims:
all of them were expressed by name.

I even weighed unto their hand six hundred and fifty talents
of silver, and silver vessels an hundred talents, \add and\add* of
gold an hundred talents;

And they made proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem unto all the
children of the captivity, that they should gather themselves together
unto Jerusalem;
